            <!-- Clause 11 -->
            <p>
                <span class="clause-title">11. LEGAL CONSTRUCTION:</span>
                In case any one or more of the provisions contained in this Agreement shall be held to be invalid in any respect, such shall not affect any other provisions of this Agreement.
            </p>

            <!-- Clause 12 -->
            <p>
                <span class="clause-title">12.</span>
                California law does not require an Attorney to, and Attorney does not, carry professional liability insurance.
            </p>

            <!-- Clause 13 -->
            <p>
                <span class="clause-title">13. CONFIDENTIALITY OF SETTLEMENTS:</span>
                Neither Firm nor any of its attorneys are able to be bound by confidentiality provisions in settlements which would in the opinion of the Firm interfere with the prosecution of other clients' cases.
            </p>

